[32m+[m[32m# Activating MCP Servers in Cursor[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mYour MCP configuration is in `.cursor/mcp.json` with the following servers:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Configured MCP Servers[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m1. **task-master-ai** - Task management and project planning[m
[32m+[m[32m2. **context7** - Upstash Context7 for enhanced context[m
[32m+[m[32m3. **github** - GitHub Copilot integration[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Activation Steps[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m1. **Restart Cursor IDE**[m
[32m+[m[32m   - Close and reopen Cursor to load the MCP configuration[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m2. **Check MCP Status**[m
[32m+[m[32m   - Open Cursor Settings (Ctrl+, or Cmd+,)[m
[32m+[m[32m   - Navigate to "Features" > "Model Context Protocol"[m
[32m+[m[32m   - Verify the servers are listed and active[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m3. **Verify Environment Variables**[m
[32m+[m[32m   The following API keys are referenced (set as environment variables):[m
[32m+[m[32m   - `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`[m
[32m+[m[32m   - `PERPLEXITY_API_KEY`[m
[32m+[m[32m   - `OPENAI_API_KEY`[m
[32m+[m[32m   - `GOOGLE_API_KEY`[m
[32m+[m[32m   - `XAI_API_KEY`[m
[32m+[m[32m   - `OPENROUTER_API_KEY`[m
[32m+[m[32m   - `MISTRAL_API_KEY`[m
[32m+[m[32m   - `AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY`[m
[32m+[m[32m   - `OLLAMA_API_KEY`[m
[32m+[m[32m   - `CONTEXT7_API_KEY`[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m4. **Test MCP Resources**[m
[32m+[m[32m   - After restart, you should see MCP resources available[m
[32m+[m[32m   - Try asking me to list available resources or use task-master commands[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Troubleshooting[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- If MCPs don't appear, check Cursor's output panel for MCP-related errors[m
[32m+[m[32m- Ensure all required environment variables are set[m
[32m+[m[32m- Verify npx is available in your PATH[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m
